Data Analysis Project
Description
This Python project performs in-depth numerical and text analysis through various functions. It can calculate statistical measures, identify textual patterns, and produce both terminal and file outputs based on user-provided data.

Installation
Clone the repository to your local machine.
Ensure Python 3.6+ is installed.
Install required packages: pip install -r requirements.txt.
Usage
Run the program by executing:


python analysis_program.py
You will be prompted to enter the names of the input and output files when running the script.

Features
Statistical Calculations: Max, min, total, median, mode, variance, and standard deviation.
Text Analysis: Identifies the longest word and performs frequency analysis.
Output Handling: Outputs results to both the console and a specified file.
Contributing
Contributions are welcome. Please fork the project, create a new branch for your contribution, and submit a pull request.

